{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014KumVp2vcsXQZosJuk45bi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The root cause is clear: the ConfigMap has `discovery.seed_hosts` but is missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. In Elasticsearch 7.x, for a fresh cluster formation, you need `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to bootstrap the cluster. Without it, nodes can't elect a master.\n\nHowever, the constraint says \"Bootstrap-only settings are removed after the cluster forms.\" This means:\n1. First, add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the ConfigMap to allow initial cluster formation\n2. After the cluster forms, remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the config (since it's a bootstrap-only setting that should not be present after the cluster is running)\n3. Restart the pods to pick up the new configuration and let the cluster form\n4. Once the cluster is healthy with a master elected, remove the bootstrap setting and do another rolling restart to confirm stability\n\nLet me examine the current logs to verify this is what's happening.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3359,"cache_read_input_tokens":32031,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3359},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5eea0396-424a-4969-ad65-a5a0172c1748","uuid":"39e3a4c8-93a3-4b06-b19a-82272bdb64da","request_id":"req_011CcMo6r72JojwWpYK5YXny"}
