{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UPhVgWBEjSASEnDaSB6uXd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The root cause is confirmed: `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is empty. All 3 nodes can see each other (they've discovered each other), but they can't elect a master because `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is not set.\n\nThe fix:\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [\"es-cluster-0\", \"es-cluster-1\", \"es-cluster-2\"]` to the ConfigMap\n2. Delete all 3 pods to restart them and pick up the new config\n3. Wait for the cluster to form and elect a master\n4. Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap (it's a bootstrap-only setting)\n5. Verify the cluster stays healthy with a rolling restart\n\nThe key insight is that `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is only needed for the very first bootstrap of a fresh cluster. Once the cluster has formed and persisted its state, this setting must be removed to avoid issues if the cluster needs to re-bootstrap. Since we're working within the constraint of using existing resources, I'll patch the ConfigMap, delete all pods simultaneously so the StatefulSet recreates them with the new configuration, and then wait for the nodes to rejoin and form the cluster.\n\nOnce everything's healthy, I'll remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap and do a rolling restart to confirm the cluster remains stable without the bootstrap setting. The reason this works is that after the initial bootstrap, each node has the cluster UUID and state persisted locally, so subsequent restarts only need `discovery.seed_hosts` to find the master—Elasticsearch actually recommends removing this setting after the first successful bootstrap to prevent accidental re-bootstrapping.\n\nNow let me execute this fix.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":851,"cache_read_input_tokens":39163,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":851},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5eea0396-424a-4969-ad65-a5a0172c1748","uuid":"65e69e65-e86f-4f57-a9c2-fa31a11b8043","request_id":"req_011CcMoBEpNcKfJNYdWMjEzf"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UPhVgWBEjSASEnDaSB6uXd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confirmed: all 3 nodes discovered each other but `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is empty, so no master can be elected. The fix is to add it to the ConfigMap, restart the pods to form the cluster, then remove it (it's bootstrap-only).\n\n**Step 1: Patch ConfigMap to add `cluster.initial_master_nodes`**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":851,"cache_read_input_tokens":39163,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":851},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5eea0396-424a-4969-ad65-a5a0172c1748","uuid":"6fdfb348-e94b-4aca-a7fd-5aa625bd0a24","request_id":"req_011CcMoBEpNcKfJNYdWMjEzf"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UPhVgWBEjSASEnDaSB6uXd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Uqto4DsJyxQeXdPCXeA4WF","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n elasticsearch patch configmap es-config --type=json -p='[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"key\":\"elasticsearch.yml\",\"path\":\"/data/elasticsearch.yml\",\"value\":\"cluster.name: es-cluster\\nnode.name: ${POD_NAME}\\nnode.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]\\nnetwork.host: 0.0.0.0\\ndiscovery.seed_hosts:\\n  - es-cluster-0.es-cluster\\n  - es-cluster-1.es-cluster\\n  - es-cluster-2.es-cluster\\ncluster.initial_master_nodes:\\n  - es-cluster-0\\n  - es-cluster-1\\n  - es-cluster-2\\nnode.store.allow_mmap: false\\n\"}]'","description":"Add cluster.initial_master_nodes to ConfigMap"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":851,"cache_read_input_tokens":39163,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":851},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5eea0396-424a-4969-ad65-a5a0172c1748","uuid":"47387087-0ec1-4407-9186-afc9b330a233","request_id":"req_011CcMoBEpNcKfJNYdWMjEzf"}
