{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Q8Y6wHn3fdW5HxBVzE5vUV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals achieved:\n\n- **Cluster status: green**, 3 nodes, master elected (`es-cluster-2`, marked `*`)\n- **Bootstrap setting removed**: `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is no longer in the ConfigMap\n- **Rolling restart completed**: all 3 pods restarted sequentially on revision `es-cluster-6b876d5676` and the cluster stayed healthy throughout\n\n**Root cause**: The `es-config` ConfigMap was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, which ES 7.x requires for the very first cluster bootstrap. Without it, nodes discover each other via `discovery.seed_hosts` but cannot elect a master because no initial voting configuration is established.\n\n**Fix applied**:\n1. Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2]` to the ConfigMap and restarted all pods — cluster bootstrapped and elected a master.\n2. Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap — this is intentional: after bootstrap the cluster state is persisted to the data PVCs, so the setting must not remain or it risks accidental re-bootstrapping on future restarts.\n3. Rolling restart confirmed the cluster survives restarts with only `discovery.seed_hosts` (no bootstrap setting needed once the cluster is formed)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":652,"cache_read_input_tokens":48673,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":652},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5eea0396-424a-4969-ad65-a5a0172c1748","uuid":"f38e08c6-8bb4-4185-9d0f-28c68beca1bf","request_id":"req_011CcMpZDgthHLMYB6itURrr"}
